OL,3,CWoman shares difficulties of battling
OL,4,Ccancer twice in her 20s
OL,6,FIn the middle of the Covid-19
OL,7,Fpandemic, aged 23, Sophie received the
OL,8,Fdevastating news that she had been
OL,9,Fdiagnosed with stage 4 Non-Hodgkins
OL,10,FLymphoma - a type of blood cancer.
OL,12,FOvernight she went from living her
OL,13,Flife to fighting for it.
OL,15,FSophie underwent multiple rounds of
OL,16,Fchemotherapy and radiotherapy to
OL,17,Fremove a melon-sized tumour near her
OL,18,Fheart, and, in May 2021, received the
OL,19,Fall clear from doctors
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G2/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1781179881
OL,3,CWoman shares difficulties of battling
OL,4,Ccancer twice in her 20s
OL,6,FBut by the end of 2023 she was hit
OL,7,Fwith yet another major health setback,
OL,8,Fwhen doctors diagnosed her with a new,
OL,9,Fseparate cancer in her thyroid.
OL,11,FSophie is now trying to raise
OL,12,Fawareness of the difficulties that she
OL,13,Fand other young people can face after
OL,14,Ffinding out they have cancer in their
OL,15,F20s.
OL,17,FSubscribe for free to our weekly
OL,18,Fnewsletter for exclusive and original
OL,19,Fcoverage from ITV News. Direct to your
OL,20,Finbox every Friday morning.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
